# Feature Spec Files

## Required sections

Every spec in `docs/specs/features/` must have:
- Status (draft → approved → in-progress → implemented)
- Problem, Scope, Acceptance criteria
- Files affected (explicit list)
- API/UI changes if applicable

## Template

Copy from `.cursor/skills/spec-driven-dev/feature-spec-template.md`

## Status transitions

- `draft` — AI or dev writing, not ready to implement
- `approved` — ready for implementation
- `in-progress` — active development
- `implemented` — done, STATE.md updated
- `deprecated` — superseded, do not implement

## Do not

- Put implementation details that belong in code comments
- Duplicate content from STATE.md (link instead)
- Leave acceptance criteria vague ("works correctly")

## After status → implemented

Trigger `update-memory` skill to sync STATE.md.
